  "field": "economics",
  "role": "object",
  "bullets": [
   "Firm-level panel of all listed Chinese cultural enterprises in film, music, publishing and interactive media from 2020 to 2024, measuring AIGC adoption intensity.",
   "No language model is applied by the researchers; identification uses difference-in-differences on staggered provincial licensing enforcement plus an event study around Cyberspace Administration announcements.",
   "Governance quality significantly shapes the scale of AIGC-driven labour displacement, state-affiliated platforms gain compliance advantages, and simulations suggest better provincial regulation reduces creative-workforce displacement."
  ],
